    • Method Detail

      • checkIntegrity

        public void checkIntegrity(SourceCodeFileProvider sourceCodeFileProvider,
                           File pcmRepositoryFile)
        Checks the integrity of the input file. This means to check the hash sums in the file against against those calculated for the source code files provided by the given sourceCodeFileProvider and the one for the provided pcmRepositoryFile.

        If anything, either the integrity check or reading in the input file, fails, the method will report to the failure API.

        Parameters:
        sourceCodeFileProvider - The provider for source code files for which hash sums should be checked.
        pcmRepositoryFile - The PCM repository file to check the hash sum for.

      • getPcmSourceLinkRepository

        public de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.core.pcmsourcestatementlink.PcmSourceStatementLinkRepository getPcmSourceLinkRepository()
        Gets the source link repository that was read in from the input file. If reading in the input file fails, the method will report to the failure API.
        Returns:
        The repository that was read in from the input file.
